Ad Text:
12 + 12 + 12 month contract 
Must hold NV1 Security Clearance
Cloud-based analytics platform, advanced analytics & AI

Our client, a law enforcement & intelligence agency, require the services of a Lead Data Engineer to design and evolve analytics capability across a hybrid cloud environment.

Duties of the Lead Data Engineer

Assist in the stand up of a cloud analytics platform using contemporary cloud-native & hybrid data engineering patterns;
Design & implement priority data pipelines aligned to a Medallion-style layered architecture, supporting repeatable ingestion, transformation & analytics workflows;
Implement modern DataOps/DevOps practices for data engineering, infrastructure-as-code, automated testing, release management, & operational runbooks;
Implement monitoring/observability & operational controls;
Build scalable data engineering solutions using distributed processing technologies;
Apply awareness of enterprise integration patterns to deliver robust and reliable integration across cloud and on‑premise environments.

 Desirable skills and qualifications include:

Experience working within modern Azure, Microsoft Fabric & Purview ecosystems, with an understanding of cloud‑native analytics & governance capabilities;
Experience enabling data science & advanced analytics capability on cloud or on-prem data platforms;
Experience working with graph databases for graph-enabled analytics;
Experience applying enterprise integration patterns (e.g., streaming ingestion, CDC/mirroring, event‑driven orchestration, hybrid integration or virtualisation) to support reliable data movement & interoperability across systems;
Experience applying data mesh type architectural patterns to support governed, scalable & domain‑aligned data products;
Experience with MLOps;
Experience working within an Intelligence context.

How to Apply 
For a copy of the full job description, including the application instructions, please get in touch with Coral at Recruitment Hive by clicking the Quick Apply button. Alternatively you can reach Coral on (02) 6299 1006 to discuss further. 

Please note that applications close on Tuesday the 7th of April 2026 at 11am. Recruitment Hive welcome late applications to be considered for future opportunities. 


Job ID: CW667345  | LH-05932
 

We Value Diversity 
The Recruitment Hive is a proud Equal Opportunity Employer. We recognise the value of diverse perspectives and experience and are committed to an inclusive workplace where everyone feels valued and respected for who they are. We encourage people with disability, indigenous, veterans and people of all backgrounds.

NV2 SECURITY CLEARANCE REQUIRED
 
The opportunity
Our Federal Government client is seeking a talented and driven person to contribute to the implementation of development engagement in the Pacific. 
  
We are looking for individuals with a current NV2 who can write analytical assessments, synthesize all source info to write the assessments, exercise good judgement / operate strictly on a need to know, take direction well and work autonomously in a reactive or fluid environment, be a team player and who is forward leaning. This role requires an individual with good analytical/written skills who can hit the ground running.  We have a lot of work to get through in the contact period, so we don’t have the luxury of time to spend months training someone to write analytical assessments. An experienced (intelligence) analyst with good regional geopolitical / Pacific foreign policy nous would be our ideal candidate, or someone with a closely aligned skillset to these requirements.  We don’t require an experienced senior manager, program manager, engagement specialist, or someone with lots of operational, UN or offshore experience for this role – it is the analytical and written skills which are the core skills required.


The role is expected to focus on:

foreign policy research and analysis;
program management, implementation and administration;
ICT database coordination, management and input functions;
administrative and logistical support for the work unit.
Your application should highlight your specific capability and experience in one or more of the above areas.


Position summary
As a Foreign Policy Officer / Analyst you will be part of a team that supports Australia’s Pacific engagement.  You will engage across the Office of the Pacific and with Pacific posts to inform implementation of Australia Pacific Leaders Program. You will have a strong capacity for policy nuance.


 Key duties may include:

undertaking foreign policy research and analysis to support Australia’s Pacific engagement;
contributing to Australia Pacific Leaders Program’s (APLP) monitoring and evaluation;
undertaking data analytics and briefing functions to support the APLP, including engaging with a wide variety of stakeholders;
supporting the administrative and logistical requirements of the work unit; and
promoting a positive team culture where staff work collegiately with a shared sense of purpose and build capability within the team by coaching others and providing feedback.
   
Our ideal candidate
We’re looking for high-performing people with experience in policy and/or program management.

Our ideal candidate will:

have demonstrated knowledge in an area of focus relevant to the department as outlined under ‘The Opportunity’ above, plus an understanding of global affairs;
have demonstrated ability to undertake policy research and analysis;
make decisions and recommendations using professional judgement and expertise in a complex environment, governed by the application of policies and best-practice principles;
be capable of developing and managing relationships with stakeholders to achieve work area goals;
have strong written and verbal communication skills;
be capable of prioritising and managing tasks, operating under broad direction exercising independence, and escalating issues that may have an impact on the work area;
demonstrate the ability to contribute positively to a workplace culture that values diversity and inclusivity; and
an understanding of ICT systems and administration (desired);
